DESCRIPTION: Test voltage across and inspect the lamp indicator (the small parallel bulb) during both lamp-on and lamp-off events, to see if it is receiving voltage and lighting up accordingly. This can help establish if power reaches any part of the load module during the fault event, narrowing down if the issue is before or at the main lamp.,
RESULT: The Internal Indicator Lamp is not lit, and both terminals show approximately 0 V relative to ground. There is no observable internal fault in the indicator lamp itself. Power does not appear to be reaching this part of the circuit during the test event.
